T - 
public class BFSDistanceLabeler<T>
extends java.lang.Object

BFSDistanceLabeler labels each node in the graph according to the BFS distance from the start node(s).

Author:
Scott White, Sabina Sara Pfister - adaptation for Cytoscape

labelDistances

public void labelDistances(DynNetworkSnapshot<T> graph,
                           java.util.Set<org.cytoscape.model.CyNode> rootSet)
Computes the distances of all the node from the starting root nodes. If there is more than one root node the minimum distance from each root node is used as the designated distance to a given node. Also keeps track of the predecessors of each node traversed as well as the order of nodes traversed.

Parameters:
graph - the graph to label
rootSet - the set of starting vertices to traverse from

labelDistances

public void labelDistances(DynNetworkSnapshot<T> graph,
                           org.cytoscape.model.CyNode root)
Computes the distances of all the node from the specified root node. Also keeps track of the predecessors of each node traversed as well as the order of nodes traversed.

Parameters:
graph - the graph to label
root - the single starting node to traverse from

getDistanceDecorator

public java.util.Map<org.cytoscape.model.CyNode,java.lang.Number> getDistanceDecorator()
Returns a map from nodes to minimum distances from the original source(s). Must be called after labelDistances in order to contain valid data.

Returns:
node map
